			<p class="grayBox"><strong>Hi Rosa!</strong> - Pale, Crystal, and Munich with a touch of Chocolate malt for color. Malty sweetness starts this classic amber off with just enough hops to balance out the rich malt character. 4.5% 30IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler, 22oz bottle $4.95</p>		

			<p><strong>Coal Creek Porter</strong> - A blend of dark malts and crystal malts gives our Porter a rich and smooth texture with a chocolatey finish. Hopped with MAgnum, Liberty and Centennial. 5.4%<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler, 22oz bottle $4.95</p>

			<p class="grayBox"><strong>Baghwan's Best IPA</strong> - A balanced English inspired IPA with a West Coast twist. Our first IPA and a Washington beer changer. Leading the way for more to come. Brewed with Magnum, Columbus, Cascade and Centennial. Dry hopped with Cascades. 6% 60IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler, 22oz bottle $4.95</p>

			<p><strong>Scarlet Fire IPA</strong> - Bigger and hoppier than Baghwan's. Brewed with a technique known as First Wort Hopping. Creating a boldhop flavor with a touch of grapefruit in the finish. Dry hopped with centennial. 6.3% 65 IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler</p>

			<h2><u>Rotators</u></h2>

			<p class="grayBox"><strong>Blind Illusion Imperial IPA</strong> - 2 row, Crystal 15, Wheat and Vienna malts combined with Columbus, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, and mosaic hops gives the imperial IPA notes of citrus and grape. 9.5% 75 IBUs<br>
			$5.5 tulips</p>		

			<p><strong>Breakfast Cereal Killer Stout</strong> - Brewed with 20 lbs. of breakfast cereal, 8 lbs. of Theo's chocolate coco nibs and 5 lbs of Stumptown coffee beans. This is one big chewy imperial stout with tons of layers.<br>
			$5 tulips</p>

			<p class="grayBox"><strong>Wet Coast</strong> - Brewed with 30% corn to give it a classic American Lager flavor  and complemented with a healthy dose of Sazz and Amarillo hops. This beer has a soft citris aroma and a hint of sea breeze. 6.3%<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler</p>		

			<p><strong>Icculus XPA</strong> - A solid citrus profile with a dry bitter finish. Brewed with 2 row, Crystal 15, Wheat, and Vienne malts. Hopped with Nelson Sauvin, Citra with a touch of Amarillo and Cascade. 5.8% 50 IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler</p>

			<p class="grayBox"><strong>Pacific Reflection Pale Ale</strong> - A juicy and tropical pale ale with flavors of passion fruit mango and citrus. Brewed with Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Cascade, Centennial, and Mosaic Hops. 5.6% 40 IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler</p>

			<p><strong>Demi Bhag ISA</strong> - A session version of the IPA that started it all. Dank, piney and citrusy hop aromas lead to easy drinkings with a smooth finish. 4.8% 37 IBUs<br>
			$5 pints, $16.25 pitcher, $12.25 growler</p>

